{
  "texts": [
    "For example, polymorphisms in taste receptor genes, such as TAS2R38, can lead to different perceptions of the same bitter compound.",
    "Additionally, cultural factors affect early exposure to certain flavors, which can shape lifelong taste preferences.",
    "This variability necessitates the development of adaptive AI systems that can dynamically analyze large datasets and tailor flavor profiles.",
    "By incorporating physiological data, such as genetic markers, along with consumer feedback, these models can predict individual preferences more accurately.",
    "Such improvements can significantly enhance consumer satisfaction and product acceptance."
  ]
}